Pakistani troops fired on Indian security forces who had fired on hundreds of Pakistani  protesters trying to cross the cease-fire line dividing Kashmir.
At least three  demonstrators were killed and 31 wounded in the Sunday skirmish.
This was the second  Pakistani demonstration to show support for the Moslem separatist movement in India's  state of Jammu-Kashmir.
Pakistani and Indian diplomats are meeting in Islamabad and  New Delhi.
In the last 40 years, the two nations have gone to war twice over the 640- mile line.
At least 85 people have been killed since the recent flare-up began on January  20. 
